clogged on 3rd stroke while passing tape trying to suck up what was pushed past the tape

pushed the cheerios forward and had too much suction under the brush and never released the suction it had to the floor even when passing the tape twice, the brush was still suctioning hard on the floor pushing all the cheerios forward out of testing box.

clogged on 3rd stroke while passing tape trying to suck up what was pushed past the tape too fast all at  once and started to clog in the inlet from cheerio pieces blocking. vac didnt turn off from clog, after 4th stroke, you can hear the vac hit a clog and then start to hear the vac get louder and can hear a steady suction from the vac while its trying to clear the clog while its still running

clogged the same way for cheerios as the last run. i noticed if i turn the vac on and have brush flat on the floor and while i put it to max without lifting the brush, after its on max and i start the test strokes thats when the vac is unable to pick soil. BUT if i turn it on and put it on max without having the brush on the floor before starting the test strokes, then the brush is able to pick up any of the soils. I only had this problem with this nozzle and will make a observation slide.

started to clog on 1st passing of the tape and when reached the end of test, it didnt shut off from the clog, it kept trying to clear the air way with no visual alert of clog but there was the sound of the clog and the sound of the vacuum over working to clear the inlet and airway.
pushed cheerios passed tape both passes. it looks as if it couldnt get over the cheerios and only could push in front of brush.

Handle is comfortable. Brush pick up capability

does not push much for cheerios/rice. while going forward/backward the vac sucks up  50% of the soil it runs over immediately on the first stroke. not many soils get caught behind the brush. 2nd stroke it sucks up the rest of the soils in its path.
For rice, sometimes it seems the brush doesnt get under all the rice immediately. it pushes some soils as it does tend to pick up most of the mess.
would suck up the cheerios that were immediately in its path, then push the soils that arent directly in front of the brush. leading it not able to pick up the soils it kept pushing further.
seems to suck up the most of the sand the first stroke, the 2nd stroke helps pick up the rest. Sand grains are left behind the brush after each run.

does not push any sand in front of the brush. appears to suck up all the sand in its path both strokes. after each run, there is a small lump of sand left behind the testing box behind the brush each time.

vac leaves barely no sand grains after both strokes. doesnt appear to push any sand in front of the brush. For cheerios, the brush is capable of sucking up the cheerios that are in its path and not dragging any behind. as it runs over the cheerios and sucks up about 50% of what it ran over and leaving what it didnt left in the box, some pushed alittle outside the box in front of it.
pushes some cheerios/rice that wasnt directly in front of brush.
Immediately sucks up the sand that it runs over.
Rice run, the vac didnt run past any rice, it was capable of just picking up what was in front of it without pushing any foward.
was not really pushing cheerios forward. it was mostly sucking up the cheerios that was directly in front of it.
was pushing some cheerios forward the first stroke alittle past the testing box.
Some sand/rice fly-aways as it runs forward and sometimes backwards.
Picks up some of the cheerios on the first stroke, pushes what isnt directly in front of the brush. Some single soils fly to the side as it goes forward/backward.
For rice, it would immediately suck up the rice that it was running over, not all but about 50% of it the first stroke. Some flyaways.
